<p><strong>Where do these statistics come from?</strong></p>
<p>All statistics come from named, verifiable sources including Superlines, Semrush, Ahrefs, First Page Sage, Gartner, Incremys, and academic research. Each stat includes a direct source link.</p>
<p><strong>What is GEO (Generative Engine Optimization)?</strong></p>
<p>GEO is the practice of optimizing content so AI search engines cite and reference it. Unlike traditional SEO (which targets Google rankings), GEO targets visibility in ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews, and other AI platforms. Learn more in our <a href="/blog/generative-engine-optimization-guide/">generative engine optimization guide</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Is GEO replacing traditional SEO?</strong></p>
<p>No. GEO complements SEO. 76.1% of URLs cited in AI Overviews also rank in Google's top 10. Strong traditional SEO remains the foundation. GEO adds a new visibility layer on top.</p>
<p><strong>How does AI citation differ from traditional search ranking?</strong></p>
<p>80% of URLs cited by AI platforms do not rank in Google's top 100. AI uses different signals: content structure, freshness, statistics, author authority, and readability. Traditional ranking factors like backlinks matter less for AI citation.</p>
<p>GEO is the fastest-growing segment of search marketing. The data shows it clearly: AI traffic converts higher, the market grows at 50.5% CAGR, and most competitors have no strategy yet. The businesses that act on these statistics now will own AI visibility for years.</p>
